32  class ASTStmtWriter : public StmtVisitor<ASTStmtWriter, void> {
33  ASTWriter &Writer;
34  ASTRecordWriter Record;
35 
36  serialization::StmtCode Code;
37  unsigned AbbrevToUse;
38 
39  public:
40  ASTStmtWriter(ASTWriter &Writer, ASTWriter::RecordData &Record)
41  : Writer(Writer), Record(Writer, Record),
42  Code(serialization::STMT_NULL_PTR), AbbrevToUse(0) {}
43 
44  ASTStmtWriter(const ASTStmtWriter&) = delete;
45 
46  uint64_t Emit() {
47  assert(Code != serialization::STMT_NULL_PTR &&
48  "unhandled sub-statement writing AST file");
49  return Record.EmitStmt(Code, AbbrevToUse);
50  }

57  void Visit##Type(Type *);

62 void ASTStmtWriter::AddTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(
63  const ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo &ArgInfo, const TemplateArgumentLoc *Args) {
64  Record.AddSourceLocation(ArgInfo.TemplateKWLoc);
65  Record.AddSourceLocation(ArgInfo.LAngleLoc);
66  Record.AddSourceLocation(ArgInfo.RAngleLoc);
67  for (unsigned i = 0; i != ArgInfo.NumTemplateArgs; ++i)
68  Record.AddTemplateArgumentLoc(Args[i]);

98 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitCaseStmt(CaseStmt *S) {
99  VisitSwitchCase(S);
100  Record.push_back(S->caseStmtIsGNURange());
101  Record.AddStmt(S->getLHS());
102  Record.AddStmt(S->getSubStmt());
103  if (S->caseStmtIsGNURange()) {
104  Record.AddStmt(S->getRHS());
105  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getEllipsisLoc());
106  }
107  Code = serialization::STMT_CASE;

134 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitIfStmt(IfStmt *S) {
135  VisitStmt(S);
136 
137  bool HasElse = S->getElse() != nullptr;
138  bool HasVar = S->getConditionVariableDeclStmt() != nullptr;
139  bool HasInit = S->getInit() != nullptr;
140 
141  Record.push_back(HasElse);
142  Record.push_back(HasVar);
143  Record.push_back(HasInit);
144  Record.push_back(static_cast<uint64_t>(S->getStatementKind()));
145  Record.AddStmt(S->getCond());
146  Record.AddStmt(S->getThen());
147  if (HasElse)
148  Record.AddStmt(S->getElse());
149  if (HasVar)
150  Record.AddDeclRef(S->getConditionVariable());
151  if (HasInit)
152  Record.AddStmt(S->getInit());
153 
154  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getIfLoc());
155  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getLParenLoc());
156  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getRParenLoc());
157  if (HasElse)
158  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getElseLoc());
159 
160  Code = serialization::STMT_IF;
161 }

163 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitSwitchStmt(SwitchStmt *S) {
164  VisitStmt(S);
165 
166  bool HasInit = S->getInit() != nullptr;
167  bool HasVar = S->getConditionVariableDeclStmt() != nullptr;
168  Record.push_back(HasInit);
169  Record.push_back(HasVar);
170  Record.push_back(S->isAllEnumCasesCovered());
171 
172  Record.AddStmt(S->getCond());
173  Record.AddStmt(S->getBody());
174  if (HasInit)
175  Record.AddStmt(S->getInit());
176  if (HasVar)
177  Record.AddDeclRef(S->getConditionVariable());
178 
179  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getSwitchLoc());
180  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getLParenLoc());
181  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getRParenLoc());
182 
183  for (SwitchCase *SC = S->getSwitchCaseList(); SC;
184  SC = SC->getNextSwitchCase())
185  Record.push_back(Writer.RecordSwitchCaseID(SC));
186  Code = serialization::STMT_SWITCH;
187 }

291 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitGCCAsmStmt(GCCAsmStmt *S) {
292  VisitAsmStmt(S);
293  Record.push_back(S->getNumLabels());
294  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getRParenLoc());
295  Record.AddStmt(S->getAsmString());
296 
297  // Outputs
298  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumOutputs(); I != N; ++I) {
299  Record.AddIdentifierRef(S->getOutputIdentifier(I));
300  Record.AddStmt(S->getOutputConstraintLiteral(I));
301  Record.AddStmt(S->getOutputExpr(I));
302  }
303 
304  // Inputs
305  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumInputs(); I != N; ++I) {
306  Record.AddIdentifierRef(S->getInputIdentifier(I));
307  Record.AddStmt(S->getInputConstraintLiteral(I));
308  Record.AddStmt(S->getInputExpr(I));
309  }
310 
311  // Clobbers
312  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumClobbers(); I != N; ++I)
313  Record.AddStmt(S->getClobberStringLiteral(I));
314 
315  // Labels
316  for (auto *E : S->labels()) Record.AddStmt(E);
317 
318  Code = serialization::STMT_GCCASM;
319 }

321 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitMSAsmStmt(MSAsmStmt *S) {
322  VisitAsmStmt(S);
323  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getLBraceLoc());
324  Record.AddSourceLocation(S->getEndLoc());
325  Record.push_back(S->getNumAsmToks());
326  Record.AddString(S->getAsmString());
327 
328  // Tokens
329  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumAsmToks(); I != N; ++I) {
330  // FIXME: Move this to ASTRecordWriter?
331  Writer.AddToken(S->getAsmToks()[I], Record.getRecordData());
332  }
333 
334  // Clobbers
335  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumClobbers(); I != N; ++I) {
336  Record.AddString(S->getClobber(I));
337  }
338 
339  // Outputs
340  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumOutputs(); I != N; ++I) {
341  Record.AddStmt(S->getOutputExpr(I));
342  Record.AddString(S->getOutputConstraint(I));
343  }
344 
345  // Inputs
346  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumInputs(); I != N; ++I) {
347  Record.AddStmt(S->getInputExpr(I));
348  Record.AddString(S->getInputConstraint(I));
349  }
350 
351  Code = serialization::STMT_MSASM;
352 }

398 static void
399 addConstraintSatisfaction(ASTRecordWriter &Record,
400  const ASTConstraintSatisfaction &Satisfaction) {
401  Record.push_back(Satisfaction.IsSatisfied);
402  if (!Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
403  Record.push_back(Satisfaction.NumRecords);
404  for (const auto &DetailRecord : Satisfaction) {
405  Record.AddStmt(const_cast<Expr *>(DetailRecord.first));
406  auto *E = DetailRecord.second.dyn_cast<Expr *>();
407  Record.push_back(E == nullptr);
408  if (E)
409  Record.AddStmt(E);
410  else {
411  auto *Diag = DetailRecord.second.get<std::pair<SourceLocation,
412  StringRef> *>();
413  Record.AddSourceLocation(Diag->first);
414  Record.AddString(Diag->second);
415  }
416  }
417  }
418 }

429 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitConceptSpecializationExpr(
430  ConceptSpecializationExpr *E) {
431  VisitExpr(E);
432  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TemplateArgs = E->getTemplateArguments();
433  Record.push_back(TemplateArgs.size());
434  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
435  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getTemplateKWLoc());
436  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(E->getConceptNameInfo());
437  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getNamedConcept());
438  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getFoundDecl());
439  Record.AddASTTemplateArgumentListInfo(E->getTemplateArgsAsWritten());
440  for (const TemplateArgument &Arg : TemplateArgs)
441  Record.AddTemplateArgument(Arg);
442  if (!E->isValueDependent())
443  addConstraintSatisfaction(Record, E->getSatisfaction());
444 
445  Code = serialization::EXPR_CONCEPT_SPECIALIZATION;
446 }

448 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitRequiresExpr(RequiresExpr *E) {
449  VisitExpr(E);
450  Record.push_back(E->getLocalParameters().size());
451  Record.push_back(E->getRequirements().size());
452  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->RequiresExprBits.RequiresKWLoc);
453  Record.push_back(E->RequiresExprBits.IsSatisfied);
454  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getBody());
455  for (ParmVarDecl *P : E->getLocalParameters())
456  Record.AddDeclRef(P);
457  for (concepts::Requirement *R : E->getRequirements()) {
458  if (auto *TypeReq = dyn_cast<concepts::TypeRequirement>(R)) {
459  Record.push_back(concepts::Requirement::RK_Type);
460  Record.push_back(TypeReq->Status);
461  if (TypeReq->Status == concepts::TypeRequirement::SS_SubstitutionFailure)
462  addSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record, TypeReq->getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
463  else
464  Record.AddTypeSourceInfo(TypeReq->getType());
465  } else if (auto *ExprReq = dyn_cast<concepts::ExprRequirement>(R)) {
466  Record.push_back(ExprReq->getKind());
467  Record.push_back(ExprReq->Status);
468  if (ExprReq->isExprSubstitutionFailure()) {
469  addSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record,
470  ExprReq->Value.get<concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *>());
471  } else
472  Record.AddStmt(ExprReq->Value.get<Expr *>());
473  if (ExprReq->getKind() == concepts::Requirement::RK_Compound) {
474  Record.AddSourceLocation(ExprReq->NoexceptLoc);
475  const auto &RetReq = ExprReq->getReturnTypeRequirement();
476  if (RetReq.isSubstitutionFailure()) {
477  Record.push_back(2);
478  addSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record, RetReq.getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
479  } else if (RetReq.isTypeConstraint()) {
480  Record.push_back(1);
481  Record.AddTemplateParameterList(
482  RetReq.getTypeConstraintTemplateParameterList());
483  if (ExprReq->Status >=
484  concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_ConstraintsNotSatisfied)
485  Record.AddStmt(
486  ExprReq->getReturnTypeRequirementSubstitutedConstraintExpr());
487  } else {
488  assert(RetReq.isEmpty());
489  Record.push_back(0);
490  }
491  }
492  } else {
493  auto *NestedReq = cast<concepts::NestedRequirement>(R);
494  Record.push_back(concepts::Requirement::RK_Nested);
495  Record.push_back(NestedReq->isSubstitutionFailure());
496  if (NestedReq->isSubstitutionFailure()){
497  addSubstitutionDiagnostic(Record,
498  NestedReq->getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
499  } else {
500  Record.AddStmt(NestedReq->Value.get<Expr *>());
501  if (!NestedReq->isDependent())
502  addConstraintSatisfaction(Record, *NestedReq->Satisfaction);
503  }
504  }
505  }
506  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getEndLoc());
507 
508  Code = serialization::EXPR_REQUIRES;
509 }

512 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitCapturedStmt(CapturedStmt *S) {
513  VisitStmt(S);
514  // NumCaptures
515  Record.push_back(std::distance(S->capture_begin(), S->capture_end()));
516 
517  // CapturedDecl and captured region kind
518  Record.AddDeclRef(S->getCapturedDecl());
519  Record.push_back(S->getCapturedRegionKind());
520 
521  Record.AddDeclRef(S->getCapturedRecordDecl());
522 
523  // Capture inits
524  for (auto *I : S->capture_inits())
525  Record.AddStmt(I);
526 
527  // Body
528  Record.AddStmt(S->getCapturedStmt());
529 
530  // Captures
531  for (const auto &I : S->captures()) {
532  if (I.capturesThis() || I.capturesVariableArrayType())
533  Record.AddDeclRef(nullptr);
534  else
535  Record.AddDeclRef(I.getCapturedVar());
536  Record.push_back(I.getCaptureKind());
537  Record.AddSourceLocation(I.getLocation());
538  }
539 
540  Code = serialization::STMT_CAPTURED;
541 }

543 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitExpr(Expr *E) {
544  VisitStmt(E);
545  Record.AddTypeRef(E->getType());
546  Record.push_back(E->isTypeDependent());
547  Record.push_back(E->isValueDependent());
548  Record.push_back(E->isInstantiationDependent());
549  Record.push_back(E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack());
550  Record.push_back(E->containsErrors());
551  Record.push_back(E->getValueKind());
552  Record.push_back(E->getObjectKind());
553 }

555 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitConstantExpr(ConstantExpr *E) {
556  VisitExpr(E);
557  Record.push_back(E->ConstantExprBits.ResultKind);
558 
559  Record.push_back(E->ConstantExprBits.APValueKind);
560  Record.push_back(E->ConstantExprBits.IsUnsigned);
561  Record.push_back(E->ConstantExprBits.BitWidth);
562  // HasCleanup not serialized since we can just query the APValue.
563  Record.push_back(E->ConstantExprBits.IsImmediateInvocation);
564 
565  switch (E->ConstantExprBits.ResultKind) {
566  case ConstantExpr::RSK_None:
567  break;
568  case ConstantExpr::RSK_Int64:
569  Record.push_back(E->Int64Result());
570  break;
571  case ConstantExpr::RSK_APValue:
572  Record.AddAPValue(E->APValueResult());
573  break;
574  default:
575  llvm_unreachable("unexpected ResultKind!");
576  }
577 
578  Record.AddStmt(E->getSubExpr());
579  Code = serialization::EXPR_CONSTANT;
580 }

616 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
617  VisitExpr(E);
618 
619  Record.push_back(E->hasQualifier());
620  Record.push_back(E->getDecl() != E->getFoundDecl());
621  Record.push_back(E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo());
622  Record.push_back(E->hadMultipleCandidates());
623  Record.push_back(E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture());
624  Record.push_back(E->isNonOdrUse());
625 
626  if (E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo()) {
627  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = E->getNumTemplateArgs();
628  Record.push_back(NumTemplateArgs);
629  }
630 
631  DeclarationName::NameKind nk = (E->getDecl()->getDeclName().getNameKind());
632 
633  if ((!E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo()) && (!E->hasQualifier()) &&
634  (E->getDecl() == E->getFoundDecl()) &&
635  nk == DeclarationName::Identifier &&
636  !E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture() && !E->isNonOdrUse()) {
637  AbbrevToUse = Writer.getDeclRefExprAbbrev();
638  }
639 
640  if (E->hasQualifier())
641  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
642 
643  if (E->getDecl() != E->getFoundDecl())
644  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getFoundDecl());
645 
646  if (E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo())
647  AddTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(*E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>(),
648  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>());
649 
650  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getDecl());
651  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getLocation());
652  Record.AddDeclarationNameLoc(E->DNLoc, E->getDecl()->getDeclName());
653  Code = serialization::EXPR_DECL_REF;
654 }

757 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
758  VisitExpr(E);
759  Record.push_back(E->getNumComponents());

762  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getRParenLoc());

764  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumComponents(); I != N; ++I) {
765  const OffsetOfNode &ON = E->getComponent(I);

767  Record.AddSourceLocation(ON.getSourceRange().getBegin());

784  break;

786  }

899 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
900  VisitExpr(E);
901 
902  bool HasQualifier = E->hasQualifier();
903  bool HasFoundDecl =
904  E->hasQualifierOrFoundDecl() &&
905  (E->getFoundDecl().getDecl() != E->getMemberDecl() ||
906  E->getFoundDecl().getAccess() != E->getMemberDecl()->getAccess());
907  bool HasTemplateInfo = E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo();
908  unsigned NumTemplateArgs = E->getNumTemplateArgs();
909 
910  // Write these first for easy access when deserializing, as they affect the
911  // size of the MemberExpr.
912  Record.push_back(HasQualifier);
913  Record.push_back(HasFoundDecl);
914  Record.push_back(HasTemplateInfo);
915  Record.push_back(NumTemplateArgs);
916 
917  Record.AddStmt(E->getBase());
918  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getMemberDecl());
919  Record.AddDeclarationNameLoc(E->MemberDNLoc,
920  E->getMemberDecl()->getDeclName());
921  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getMemberLoc());
922  Record.push_back(E->isArrow());
923  Record.push_back(E->hadMultipleCandidates());
924  Record.push_back(E->isNonOdrUse());
925  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getOperatorLoc());
926 
927  if (HasFoundDecl) {
928  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl = E->getFoundDecl();
929  Record.AddDeclRef(FoundDecl.getDecl());
930  Record.push_back(FoundDecl.getAccess());
931  }
932 
933  if (HasQualifier)
934  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
935 
936  if (HasTemplateInfo)
937  AddTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(*E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>(),
938  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>());
939 
940  Code = serialization::EXPR_MEMBER;
941 }

1067 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
1068  VisitExpr(E);
1069  // NOTE: only add the (possibly null) syntactic form.
1070  // No need to serialize the isSemanticForm flag and the semantic form.
1071  Record.AddStmt(E->getSyntacticForm());
1072  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getLBraceLoc());
1073  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getRBraceLoc());
1074  bool isArrayFiller = E->ArrayFillerOrUnionFieldInit.is<Expr*>();
1075  Record.push_back(isArrayFiller);
1076  if (isArrayFiller)
1077  Record.AddStmt(E->getArrayFiller());
1078  else
1079  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getInitializedFieldInUnion());
1080  Record.push_back(E->hadArrayRangeDesignator());
1081  Record.push_back(E->getNumInits());
1082  if (isArrayFiller) {
1083  // ArrayFiller may have filled "holes" due to designated initializer.
1084  // Replace them by 0 to indicate that the filler goes in that place.
1085  Expr *filler = E->getArrayFiller();
1086  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumInits(); I != N; ++I)
1087  Record.AddStmt(E->getInit(I) != filler ? E->getInit(I) : nullptr);
1088  } else {
1089  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumInits(); I != N; ++I)
1090  Record.AddStmt(E->getInit(I));
1091  }
1092  Code = serialization::EXPR_INIT_LIST;
1093 }

1095 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitDesignatedInitExpr(DesignatedInitExpr *E) {
1096  VisitExpr(E);
1097  Record.push_back(E->getNumSubExprs());
1098  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumSubExprs(); I != N; ++I)
1099  Record.AddStmt(E->getSubExpr(I));
1100  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getEqualOrColonLoc());
1101  Record.push_back(E->usesGNUSyntax());
1102  for (const DesignatedInitExpr::Designator &D : E->designators()) {
1103  if (D.isFieldDesignator()) {
1104  if (FieldDecl *Field = D.getField()) {
1105  Record.push_back(serialization::DESIG_FIELD_DECL);
1106  Record.AddDeclRef(Field);
1107  } else {
1108  Record.push_back(serialization::DESIG_FIELD_NAME);
1109  Record.AddIdentifierRef(D.getFieldName());
1110  }
1111  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getDotLoc());
1112  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getFieldLoc());
1113  } else if (D.isArrayDesignator()) {
1114  Record.push_back(serialization::DESIG_ARRAY);
1115  Record.push_back(D.getFirstExprIndex());
1116  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getLBracketLoc());
1117  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getRBracketLoc());
1118  } else {
1119  assert(D.isArrayRangeDesignator() && "Unknown designator");
1120  Record.push_back(serialization::DESIG_ARRAY_RANGE);
1121  Record.push_back(D.getFirstExprIndex());
1122  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getLBracketLoc());
1123  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getEllipsisLoc());
1124  Record.AddSourceLocation(D.getRBracketLoc());
1125  }
1126  }
1127  Code = serialization::EXPR_DESIGNATED_INIT;
1128 }

1412 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitObjCMessageExpr(ObjCMessageExpr *E) {
1413  VisitExpr(E);
1414  Record.push_back(E->getNumArgs());
1415  Record.push_back(E->getNumStoredSelLocs());
1416  Record.push_back(E->SelLocsKind);
1417  Record.push_back(E->isDelegateInitCall());
1418  Record.push_back(E->IsImplicit);
1419  Record.push_back((unsigned)E->getReceiverKind()); // FIXME: stable encoding
1420  switch (E->getReceiverKind()) {
1421  case ObjCMessageExpr::Instance:
1422  Record.AddStmt(E->getInstanceReceiver());
1423  break;
1424 
1425  case ObjCMessageExpr::Class:
1426  Record.AddTypeSourceInfo(E->getClassReceiverTypeInfo());
1427  break;
1428 
1429  case ObjCMessageExpr::SuperClass:
1430  case ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance:
1431  Record.AddTypeRef(E->getSuperType());
1432  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getSuperLoc());
1433  break;
1434  }
1435 
1436  if (E->getMethodDecl()) {
1437  Record.push_back(1);
1438  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getMethodDecl());
1439  } else {
1440  Record.push_back(0);
1441  Record.AddSelectorRef(E->getSelector());
1442  }
1443 
1444  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getLeftLoc());
1445  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getRightLoc());
1446 
1447  for (CallExpr::arg_iterator Arg = E->arg_begin(), ArgEnd = E->arg_end();
1448  Arg != ArgEnd; ++Arg)
1449  Record.AddStmt(*Arg);
1450 
1451  SourceLocation *Locs = E->getStoredSelLocs();
1452  for (unsigned i = 0, e = E->getNumStoredSelLocs(); i != e; ++i)
1453  Record.AddSourceLocation(Locs[i]);
1454 
1455  Code = serialization::EXPR_OBJC_MESSAGE_EXPR;
1456 }

1893 void ASTStmtWriter::VisitCXXDependentScopeMemberExpr(
1894  CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr *E) {
1895  VisitExpr(E);
1896 
1897  // Don't emit anything here (or if you do you will have to update
1898  // the corresponding deserialization function).
1899 
1900  Record.push_back(E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo());
1901  Record.push_back(E->getNumTemplateArgs());
1902  Record.push_back(E->hasFirstQualifierFoundInScope());
1903 
1904  if (E->hasTemplateKWAndArgsInfo()) {
1905  const ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo &ArgInfo =
1906  *E->getTrailingObjects<ASTTemplateKWAndArgsInfo>();
1907  AddTemplateKWAndArgsInfo(ArgInfo,
1908  E->getTrailingObjects<TemplateArgumentLoc>());
1909  }
1910 
1911  Record.push_back(E->isArrow());
1912  Record.AddSourceLocation(E->getOperatorLoc());
1913  Record.AddTypeRef(E->getBaseType());
1914  Record.AddNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
1915  if (!E->isImplicitAccess())
1916  Record.AddStmt(E->getBase());
1917  else
1918  Record.AddStmt(nullptr);
1919 
1920  if (E->hasFirstQualifierFoundInScope())
1921  Record.AddDeclRef(E->getFirstQualifierFoundInScope());
1922 
1923  Record.AddDeclarationNameInfo(E->MemberNameInfo);
1924  Code = serialization::EXPR_CXX_DEPENDENT_SCOPE_MEMBER;
1925 }

2681 /// Write the given substatement or subexpression to the
2682 /// bitstream.
2683 void ASTWriter::WriteSubStmt(Stmt *S) {
2684  RecordData Record;
2685  ASTStmtWriter Writer(*this, Record);
2686  ++NumStatements;
2687 
2688  if (!S) {
2689  Stream.EmitRecord(serialization::STMT_NULL_PTR, Record);
2690  return;
2691  }
2692 
2693  llvm::DenseMap<Stmt *, uint64_t>::iterator I = SubStmtEntries.find(S);
2694  if (I != SubStmtEntries.end()) {
2695  Record.push_back(I->second);
2696  Stream.EmitRecord(serialization::STMT_REF_PTR, Record);
2697  return;
2698  }
2699 
2700 #ifndef NDEBUG
2701  assert(!ParentStmts.count(S) && "There is a Stmt cycle!");
2702 
2703  struct ParentStmtInserterRAII {
2704  Stmt *S;
2705  llvm::DenseSet<Stmt *> &ParentStmts;
2706 
2707  ParentStmtInserterRAII(Stmt *S, llvm::DenseSet<Stmt *> &ParentStmts)
2708  : S(S), ParentStmts(ParentStmts) {
2709  ParentStmts.insert(S);
2710  }
2711  ~ParentStmtInserterRAII() {
2712  ParentStmts.erase(S);
2713  }
2714  };
2715 
2716  ParentStmtInserterRAII ParentStmtInserter(S, ParentStmts);
2717 #endif
2718 
2719  Writer.Visit(S);
2720 
2721  uint64_t Offset = Writer.Emit();
2722  SubStmtEntries[S] = Offset;
2723 }

2725 /// Flush all of the statements that have been added to the
2726 /// queue via AddStmt().
2727 void ASTRecordWriter::FlushStmts() {
2728  // We expect to be the only consumer of the two temporary statement maps,
2729  // assert that they are empty.
2730  assert(Writer->SubStmtEntries.empty() && "unexpected entries in sub-stmt map");
2731  assert(Writer->ParentStmts.empty() && "unexpected entries in parent stmt map");
2732 
2733  for (unsigned I = 0, N = StmtsToEmit.size(); I != N; ++I) {
2734  Writer->WriteSubStmt(StmtsToEmit[I]);
2735 
2736  assert(N == StmtsToEmit.size() && "record modified while being written!");
2737 
2738  // Note that we are at the end of a full expression. Any
2739  // expression records that follow this one are part of a different
2740  // expression.
2741  Writer->Stream.EmitRecord(serialization::STMT_STOP, ArrayRef<uint32_t>());
2742 
2743  Writer->SubStmtEntries.clear();
2744  Writer->ParentStmts.clear();
2745  }
2746 
2747  StmtsToEmit.clear();
2748 }
2749 
2750 void ASTRecordWriter::FlushSubStmts() {
2751  // For a nested statement, write out the substatements in reverse order (so
2752  // that a simple stack machine can be used when loading), and don't emit a
2753  // STMT_STOP after each one.
2754  for (unsigned I = 0, N = StmtsToEmit.size(); I != N; ++I) {
2755  Writer->WriteSubStmt(StmtsToEmit[N - I - 1]);
2756  assert(N == StmtsToEmit.size() && "record modified while being written!");
2757  }
2758 
2759  StmtsToEmit.clear();
2760 }
